## Introduction to R Markdown (taken from the R Markdown template)

This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see <http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com>.

We use it in this class so that you can write up your R code, your math work, and your written homework all in one document. You must use this for your R code. If you prefer to write down math equations by hand, you may do so as well, but attach all work to your R Markdown document whenever a homework problem requires R or a written explanation.

When you click the **Knit** button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:


