## Question 2: Math equations
You can also include math equations by surrounding them in **two dollar signs**. The following example is taken from the R Markdown template.

$$
\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \frac{1}{x} = ln(x)
$$

## Question 3: R code
You can include pieces of R code by surrounding them in **triple quotes** and after the begining triple quotes, you need to **put a label**.  The following two pieces of R code are taken from the R Markdown template.

\textbf{a)  R code snippit and output} Here is an example of R code and output.

```{r cars}
summary(cars)
```


\textbf{b) Include plots}

You can also embed plots, for example:

```{r pressure}
plot(pressure)
```
